REDESCRIPTION: Coloration (

, 

): Head unicolorous dull, light brown; carina, flagellomere 1, oral margins slightly lighter; gena dark yellow; palps brown; eyes pale red; male labellar sclerites dark, shiny brown; all setae black. Notum dull brown, with pair of faint, incomplete, paramedian lighter stripes; notopleural area, anepisternum and katepisternum slightly darker than surrounding areas; halter knob cream colored; femora light brown, remaining leg segments yellowish; wing clear, no infuscation even around crossveins. Abdomen lighter than rest of body, dark yellowish, grading posteriorly to light brown.

THORAX (
